g.text: Seems like it would be good, right? Well..😔☹️
It will never be as good as when you just use the web
chat interfaces - because it has to send BIG hidden
prompts where it describes how to use all the tools,
MCP server related stuff (if turned on)..
It sends more of this than the size of your actual
question or task you want it to be doing.
This makes it too dumb!
This applies to all the other agent software,
Cursor, Windsurf, probably does the same thing,
maybe even worse.
PLAN MODE
Instead, plan things free in AI studio,
Deepseek chat, OpenAI playground w/free tokens
using o3, o4-mini, use more than one at the same time
Or Claude in Openrouter (still cheap when its not
an agent)
Then just tell it to write a prompt for whichever
agent tools you are using (Cursor, Cline..)
Say "write a prompt for my coding agent to
complete the tasks"
Then set the agent to use an unlimited model
like GPT 4.1
